          <div class="experiment-title">
            <h2>üîç Experiment Title:</h2>
            <h3>To Determine the Acceleration Due to Gravity Using an Oscillating Mass-Spring System</h3>
          </div>
    
          <div class="experiment-section">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-bullseye me-2"></i>üéØ Learning Objectives:</h4>
            <ul class="objectives-list">
              <li>Understand the principles of simple harmonic motion (SHM) in a mass-spring system.</li>
              <li>Measure the time period for different masses attached to a spring.</li>
              <li>Establish the relationship between mass and square of time period (T¬≤ ‚àù m).</li>
              <li>Determine the spring constant and calculate the acceleration due to gravity (g).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
    
          <div class="experiment-section">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-tools me-2"></i>üõ†Ô∏è How to Perform the Experiment:</h4>
            <div class="procedure-steps">
    
              <div class="procedure-step">
                <h5>1. Set Up the Apparatus:</h5>
                <p>Fix a helical spring to a clamp stand and hang a slotted weight hanger with a pointer at the bottom end. Ensure a meter scale is placed vertically beside it.</p>
              </div>
    
              <div class="procedure-step">
                <h5>2. Zero Adjustment:</h5>
                <p>Ensure the pointer is freely hanging and aligned parallel to the scale markings without touching the scale.</p>
              </div>
    
              <div class="procedure-step">
                <h5>3. Note Initial Position:</h5>
                <p>Record the resting position of the pointer without any load on the spring.</p>
              </div>
    
              <div class="procedure-step">
                <h5>4. Add Load and Observe Extension:</h5>
                <p>Add a known weight (e.g., 150g) to the hanger. Note the new pointer position to determine spring extension.</p>
              </div>
    
              <div class="procedure-step">
                <h5>5. Initiate Oscillations:</h5>
                <p>Displace the hanger slightly (2‚Äì3 cm) and release it to start vertical oscillations.</p>
              </div>
    
              <div class="procedure-step">
                <h5>6. Time the Oscillations:</h5>
                <p>Use a stopwatch to measure the time for 30 complete oscillations.</p>
              </div>
    
              <div class="procedure-step">
                <h5>7. Repeat for Different Masses:</h5>
                <p>Increase the load in steps (e.g., 200g, 250g, 300g, 350g) and repeat the timing process for each case.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
    
